rComments: Professor Chandler is very kind and compassionate. During Covid, 25% of our grade was participation which encouraged us to get involved during class, and stay on top of the readings. Very knowledgable prof and amazing human.

Most overrated prof at UOttawa. Does not deserve the praise. Mediocre at best as a teacher. Takes decades to mark assignments. Lecture slides and a king hearted attitude are the only good thing she provides.

The best prof!! The assigned readings are not long (very reasonable). She provides thorough powerpoint slides for each class and takes the time to explain the content and answer questions. Very pleasant, highly recommend!

A true professional. She is prepared for class, her slides are crystal clear and truncate the readings perfectly. Ask her a question and she is ready to deliver a precise answer. She is always prepared, has excellent examples, and tries to engage the class as much as possible, though she is a natural lecturer. I feel fortunate to have had her.

Had her for torts and she was awesome! Taking that class made me want to take more from here.  She is not an easy marker, BUT, teaches well, which is a huge treat in this law school, where good teachers are hard to come by.  She also teaches senior courses in med-law, very good class.

Med-legal was an excellent class. Lectures were interesting, materials were not excessive. Chandler really knows her stuff, treats the class with respect, is always prepared. Awesome prof. Definitely worth taking.
